= RenameCaps =

Renames files, capitalizing the filename.

Usage: RenameCaps <options> <files...>

Options:
* '''-h, --help''' - Shows this help.
* '''-v, --version''' - Show program version.
* '''-V, --verbose''' - Enable verbose mode.
* '''-m, --media''' - rename file using special rules: "Any_file.mp3" becomes "Any File.mp3".
* '''-u, --upper''' - rename file to all capitals: "Anyfile.ext" becomes "ANYFILE.EXT".
* '''-l, --lower''' - rename file to lowercase: "Anyfile.ext" becomes "anyfile.ext". This is the default mode if no option is selected.
* '''-i, --inverse''' - inverse "artist and track names": "Bar Bar - Foo Foo.ext" becomes "Foo Foo - Bar Bar.ext"

Examples:
<pre>
RenameCaps -i "Does It Really Happen - Yes.mp3"
</pre>

